---

## Introduction

### What is Bootstrap?

Bootstrap is a popular front-end framework for building responsive, mobile-first web applications quickly and efficiently.

**Key Features:**
- Pre-built responsive components
- Powerful grid system
- Comprehensive CSS utilities
- JavaScript plugins for interactivity
- Customizable via Sass variables
- Excellent documentation
- Large community support

### Why Use Bootstrap?

| Advantage | Benefit |
|-----------|---------|
| Speed | Rapid development with pre-built components |
| Responsive | Mobile-first approach built-in |
| Consistency | Unified design across projects |
| Accessibility | WCAG compliant components |
| Community | Large ecosystem and plugins |
| Documentation | Excellent guides and examples |

### Bootstrap Versions

- **Bootstrap 3:** Grid system with `.container`, 12-column grid
- **Bootstrap 4:** Flexbox-based, improved utilities, no IE8 support
- **Bootstrap 5:** Latest (2021+), removed jQuery, enhanced utilities, CSS variables

This guide covers **Bootstrap 5** (latest version).

### Browser Support

Bootstrap 5 supports:
- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Edge (latest)
- Mobile browsers

---

## Getting Started

### Installation Methods

#### 1. CDN (Quickest)

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Bootstrap Example</title>
  
  <!-- Bootstrap CSS -->
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Hello Bootstrap!</h1>
  
  <!-- Bootstrap JS Bundle (includes Popper) -->
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

#### 2. npm Installation

```bash
npm install bootstrap
```

Then import in your project:

```javascript
// In your main.ts or main.js
import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';
import 'bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js';
```

#### 3. Download Files

Download from [getbootstrap.com](https://getbootstrap.com) and link manually.

### Viewport Meta Tag (Essential!)

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

This ensures proper rendering on mobile devices.

### Basic HTML Structure

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>My Bootstrap Site</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Content here -->
  
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

---

## Grid System

### How the Grid Works

Bootstrap uses a **12-column responsive grid system** built with flexbox.

**Understanding the 12-Column System:**
The grid divides each row into 12 equal parts. By specifying how many columns an element should span (1-12), you create flexible, proportional layouts.

**Key Concepts:**
- **Container:** Wraps row and columns (provides horizontal padding)
- **Row:** Wrapper for columns (enables flexbox layout)
- **Column:** Takes up space in 12-column grid (uses flex basis)
- **Gutters:** Space between columns (default 24px, customizable)

**ðŸ”‘ Key Points to Remember:**
- Always use `.container` or `.container-fluid` as wrapper
- Always use `.row` to group columns
- Columns should be direct children of rows
- Columns without size class (.col) share space equally
- Grid is mobile-first by default (full width on small screens)

### Container

```html
<!-- Fixed width container (responsive) -->
<div class="container">
  <!-- Max width changes at breakpoints -->
</div>

<!-- Full width container -->
<div class="container-fluid">
  <!-- Spans full width -->
</div>

<!-- Responsive containers (Bootstrap 5.2+) -->
<div class="container-sm">100% until sm breakpoint</div>
<div class="container-md">100% until md breakpoint</div>
<div class="container-lg">100% until lg breakpoint</div>
```

**Container Widths:**
| Breakpoint | Extra Small | Small | Medium | Large | X-Large | XX-Large |
|-----------|------------|-------|--------|-------|---------|----------|
| Class | - | sm | md | lg | xl | xxl |
| Width | 100% | 540px | 720px | 960px | 1140px | 1320px |

### Breakpoints

Bootstrap breakpoints allow responsive design:

```css
/* Extra small devices (phones, < 576px) */
/* No media query needed, this is the default */

/* Small devices (landscape phones, >= 576px) */
@media (min-width: 576px) { ... }

/* Medium devices (tablets, >= 768px) */
@media (min-width: 768px) { ... }

/* Large devices (desktops, >= 992px) */
@media (min-width: 992px) { ... }

/* Extra large devices (large desktops, >= 1200px) */
@media (min-width: 1200px) { ... }

/* 2XL devices (larger desktops, >= 1400px) */
@media (min-width: 1400px) { ... }
```

### Row & Columns

```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Each column can span 1-12 columns -->
    <div class="col">Column 1</div>
    <div class="col">Column 2</div>
    <div class="col">Column 3</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Column Sizing

**BASIC: Equal Width Columns**
```html
<!-- All columns take equal space (1/3 each) -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col">Column 1</div>
  <div class="col">Column 2</div>
  <div class="col">Column 3</div>
</div>
<!-- Result: Three equal columns regardless of screen size -->
```

**INTERMEDIATE: Responsive Column Sizes**
```html
<!-- Specific widths: 6 columns = 50% width -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-6">Half width (6/12 = 50%)</div>
  <div class="col-6">Half width (6/12 = 50%)</div>
</div>

<!-- Different sizes: 4 columns = 33.33% width -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-4">Column 1 (33.33%)</div>
  <div class="col-4">Column 2 (33.33%)</div>
  <div class="col-4">Column 3 (33.33%)</div>
</div>
```

**ADVANCED: Mobile-First Responsive Sizing**
```html
<!-- Multiple breakpoint classes for progressive enhancement -->
<div class="row">
  <!-- Mobile: 12 (100%), Tablet (sm+): 6 (50%), Desktop (md+): 4 (33.33%), Large (lg+): 3 (25%) -->
  <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
    Responsive column
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Practical example: Product grid -->
<div class="row">
  <!-- 1 per row on mobile, 2 on tablets, 3 on desktops, 4 on large screens -->
  <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3 col-xl-2"></div>
  <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-3 col-xl-2"></div>
  <!-- More columns -->
</div>
```

**ADVANCED: Dynamic Column Width**
```html
<!-- Col-auto: width of content (no flex grow) -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-auto">Only as wide as content</div>
  <div class="col">Fills remaining space</div>
</div>

<!-- Use case: Sidebar + Main content -->
<div class="row">
  <aside class="col-auto" style="width: 250px;">Sidebar</aside>
  <main class="col">Main content stretches to fill</main>
</div>
```

**ðŸ”‘ Key Points to Remember:**
- `.col` alone = equal-width columns (flex: 1 1 auto)
- `.col-X` = X out of 12 columns (16.67% per column)
- Each breakpoint multiplier (sm, md, lg, xl, xxl) overrides smaller ones
- Mix responsive and fixed columns for complex layouts
- Mobile-first: smaller breakpoints apply first, then override with larger ones

### Responsive Column Examples

**BASIC: Simple Two-Column Layout**
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Always 50/50 split on all screen sizes -->
    <div class="col-6">Column 1 (50%)</div>
    <div class="col-6">Column 2 (50%)</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**INTERMEDIATE: Mobile-first stacked layout**
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Mobile: Full width (col-12)
         Tablet: 2 columns (col-md-6)
         Desktop: 3 columns (col-lg-4) -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card">Box 1</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card">Box 2</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card">Box 3</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Breakdown:**
- **Mobile (< 768px):** col-12 applies â†’ full width, stacked vertically
- **Tablet (768px - 991px):** col-md-6 applies â†’ 2 columns per row
- **Desktop (â‰¥ 992px):** col-lg-4 applies â†’ 3 columns per row

**INTERMEDIATE: Sidebar layout**
```html
<div class="container mt-5">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Mobile: Sidebar below content (full width)
         Tablet+: Sidebar beside content (2/3 main, 1/3 sidebar) -->
    <main class="col-12 col-md-8">
      <h1>Main Article</h1>
      <p>Your main content here...</p>
    </main>
    <aside class="col-12 col-md-4">
      <h3>Recent Posts</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Post 1</li>
        <li>Post 2</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</div>
```

**ADVANCED: Complex Dashboard Layout**
```html
<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Header: Full width -->
    <header class="col-12 bg-light p-3 mb-4">
      Dashboard
    </header>
  </div>
  
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Sidebar: 20% on desktop, full width on mobile -->
    <nav class="col-12 col-lg-2 mb-4">
      <div class="list-group">
        <a href="#" class="list-group-item">Dashboard</a>
        <a href="#" class="list-group-item">Settings</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
    
    <!-- Main content: 80% on desktop -->
    <main class="col-12 col-lg-10">
      <!-- Row with cards: 1 on mobile, 2 on tablet, 3 on desktop -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-3">
          <div class="card">Card 1</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-3">
          <div class="card">Card 2</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-3">
          <div class="card">Card 3</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  </div>
</div>
```

**ADVANCED: Asymmetric Layout**
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- Unequal columns: 7/12 and 5/12 -->
    <main class="col-12 col-lg-7">
      <p>Main content (58.33%)</p>
    </main>
    <aside class="col-12 col-lg-5">
      <p>Sidebar (41.67%)</p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Use case: Blog with wide content area and narrower sidebar -->
```

**ðŸ”‘ Key Points to Remember:**
- Always think mobile-first: start with col-12 (full width)
- Add responsive classes as breakpoints increase
- Use col-md-6 col-lg-4 pattern for flexible layouts
- Container-fluid + responsive columns = full-width responsive
- Nesting rows/columns allows complex multi-level layouts

### Gutters (Spacing between columns)

```html
<!-- Default gutters (24px on each side = 48px total) -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col">Column 1</div>
  <div class="col">Column 2</div>
</div>

<!-- Custom gutter (1.5rem = 24px) -->
<div class="row g-3">
  <div class="col">Column 1</div>
  <div class="col">Column 2</div>
</div>

<!-- No gutters -->
<div class="row g-0">
  <div class="col">Column 1</div>
  <div class="col">Column 2</div>
</div>

<!-- Gutter sizes: g-0, g-1, g-2, g-3, g-4, g-5 -->
```

### Column Alignment

```html
<!-- Horizontal alignment -->
<div class="row justify-content-start">
  <div class="col-4">Start</div>
</div>

<div class="row justify-content-center">
  <div class="col-4">Center</div>
</div>

<div class="row justify-content-end">
  <div class="col-4">End</div>
</div>

<div class="row justify-content-around">
  <div class="col-4">Column</div>
  <div class="col-4">Column</div>
</div>

<div class="row justify-content-between">
  <div class="col-4">First</div>
  <div class="col-4">Last</div>
</div>

<!-- Vertical alignment -->
<div class="row align-items-start" style="height: 100px;">
  <div class="col">Aligned to top</div>
</div>

<div class="row align-items-center" style="height: 100px;">
  <div class="col">Centered vertically</div>
</div>

<div class="row align-items-end" style="height: 100px;">
  <div class="col">Aligned to bottom</div>
</div>
```

### Column Offset & Reordering

```html
<!-- Offset column -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-4">Column</div>
  <div class="col-4 offset-4">Offset 4</div>
</div>

<!-- Reorder columns -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4 order-md-2">Second</div>
  <div class="col-md-4 order-md-3">Third</div>
  <div class="col-md-4 order-md-1">First</div>
</div>

<!-- Nested grid -->
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-8">
      Main content
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-6">Nested column 1</div>
        <div class="col-6">Nested column 2</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-12 col-md-4">Sidebar</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

---

## Typography

### Headings

```html
<h1>Heading 1</h1>
<h2>Heading 2</h2>
<h3>Heading 3</h3>
<h4>Heading 4</h4>
<h5>Heading 5</h5>
<h6>Heading 6</h6>

<!-- Use heading classes for styling without semantic changes -->
<p class="h1">This looks like h1 but is semantic p tag</p>

<!-- Display headings (larger) -->
<h1 class="display-1">Display 1</h1>
<h1 class="display-2">Display 2</h1>
<h1 class="display-3">Display 3</h1>
<h1 class="display-4">Display 4</h1>
<h1 class="display-5">Display 5</h1>
<h1 class="display-6">Display 6</h1>
```

### Text Formatting

```html
<!-- Bold text -->
<strong>Bold text</strong>
<b>Bold text</b>

<!-- Italic text -->
<em>Emphasized text</em>
<i>Italic text</i>

<!-- Marked/highlighted -->
<mark>Highlighted text</mark>

<!-- Deleted text -->
<del>Deleted text</del>

<!-- Inserted text -->
<ins>Inserted text</ins>

<!-- Small text -->
<small>Small text</small>

<!-- Subscript & Superscript -->
<sub>Subscript</sub>
<sup>Superscript</sup>
```

### Text Alignment

```html
<p class="text-start">Start aligned</p>
<p class="text-center">Center aligned</p>
<p class="text-end">End aligned</p>
<p class="text-justify">Justified text</p>

<!-- Responsive alignment -->
<p class="text-md-start">Start on medium and up</p>
<p class="text-lg-center">Center on large and up</p>
```

### Text Transform

```html
<p class="text-lowercase">lowercased text</p>
<p class="text-uppercase">UPPERCASE TEXT</p>
<p class="text-capitalize">Capitalize each word</p>
```

### Font Weight & Style

```html
<p class="fw-light">Light weight (300)</p>
<p class="fw-normal">Normal weight (400)</p>
<p class="fw-semibold">Semibold weight (600)</p>
<p class="fw-bold">Bold weight (700)</p>

<p class="fst-italic">Italic text</p>
<p class="fst-normal">Normal style</p>
```

### Line Height

```html
<p class="lh-1">Single line height</p>
<p class="lh-sm">Small line height</p>
<p class="lh-base">Base line height</p>
<p class="lh-lg">Large line height</p>
```

---

## Colors & Backgrounds

### Color Utilities

Bootstrap provides semantic color classes:

```html
<!-- Text colors -->
<p class="text-primary">Primary text</p>
<p class="text-secondary">Secondary text</p>
<p class="text-success">Success text</p>
<p class="text-danger">Danger text</p>
<p class="text-warning">Warning text</p>
<p class="text-info">Info text</p>
<p class="text-light">Light text</p>
<p class="text-dark">Dark text</p>
<p class="text-muted">Muted text</p>
<p class="text-white">White text</p>

<!-- Background colors -->
<div class="bg-primary">Primary background</div>
<div class="bg-secondary">Secondary background</div>
<div class="bg-success">Success background</div>
<div class="bg-danger">Danger background</div>
<div class="bg-warning">Warning background</div>
<div class="bg-info">Info background</div>
<div class="bg-light">Light background</div>
<div class="bg-dark">Dark background</div>
<div class="bg-white">White background</div>

<!-- Background gradient -->
<div class="bg-gradient bg-primary">Gradient background</div>
```

### Semantic Colors

| Class | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `.text-primary` | Primary color for main actions |
| `.text-success` | Success messages, positive actions |
| `.text-danger` | Errors, dangerous actions |
| `.text-warning` | Warnings, attention needed |
| `.text-info` | Informational messages |
| `.text-muted` | Secondary, less important text |

### Custom Colors with CSS Variables

```css
:root {
  --bs-primary: #0d6efd;
  --bs-secondary: #6c757d;
  --bs-success: #198754;
  --bs-danger: #dc3545;
  --bs-warning: #ffc107;
  --bs-info: #0dcaf0;
  --bs-light: #f8f9fa;
  --bs-dark: #212529;
}
```

---

## Components

### Buttons

**BASIC: Button Types & Colors**
```html
<!-- Semantic color buttons -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary (Main actions)</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
<button class="btn btn-success">Success (Positive)</button>
<button class="btn btn-danger">Danger (Destructive)</button>
<button class="btn btn-warning">Warning (Alert)</button>
<button class="btn btn-info">Info (Information)</button>
<button class="btn btn-light">Light</button>
<button class="btn btn-dark">Dark</button>
```

**Color Usage Guide:**
- `.btn-primary`: Main call-to-action (Submit, Save, Create)
- `.btn-success`: Positive confirmations
- `.btn-danger`: Delete, Remove, Cancel operations
- `.btn-warning`: Cautions, Important notices
- `.btn-info`: Additional information

**INTERMEDIATE: Button Variants & States**
```html
<!-- Solid buttons (filled background) -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">Solid Button</button>

<!-- Outlined buttons (border only) -->
<button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Outlined Button</button>
<!-- Use case: Secondary actions, alternate options -->

<!-- Button sizes -->
<button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Large button (44px height)</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary">Default button (38px height)</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Small button (32px height)</button>

<!-- Button states -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">Normal</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary" disabled>Disabled (non-interactive)</button>
<button class="btn btn-primary" aria-pressed="true">Active/Pressed</button>
```

**ADVANCED: Button Groups & Combinations**
```html
<!-- Horizontal button group (toolbar) -->
<div class="btn-group" role="group">
  <button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Left</button>
  <button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Center</button>
  <button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Right</button>
</div>
<!-- Use case: Option selection, alignment tools -->

<!-- Vertical button group -->
<div class="btn-group-vertical" role="group">
  <button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Option 1</button>
  <button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Option 2</button>
  <button class="btn btn-outline-primary">Option 3</button>
</div>

<!-- Button with icon + text -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">
  <i class="bi bi-download"></i> Download
</button>

<!-- Button loading state -->
<button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" disabled>
  <span class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm me-2"></span>
  Loading...
</button>

<!-- Button with dropdown -->
<div class="btn-group" role="group">
  <button class="btn btn-primary">Action</button>
  <button class="btn btn-primary dropdown-toggle dropdown-toggle-split" data-bs-toggle="dropdown">
    <span class="visually-hidden">Toggle dropdown</span>
  </button>
  <ul class="dropdown-menu">
    <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Item 1</a></li>
    <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Item 2</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>
```

**ADVANCED: Dynamic Button States**
```javascript
// Toggle button state
const button = document.querySelector('.btn');
button.addEventListener('click', () => {
  button.disabled = true;
  button.innerHTML = '<span class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm me-2"></span>Loading...';
  
  // Simulate async operation
  setTimeout(() => {
    button.disabled = false;
    button.innerHTML = 'Done!';
  }, 2000);
});
```

**ðŸ”‘ Key Points to Remember:**
- `.btn` is required base class for all buttons
- Always add role="group" to button groups for accessibility
- Use semantic colors for clear user intent
- Disabled state prevents interaction and shows visual change
- Button groups are useful for toggle/selection patterns
- Outline buttons for secondary actions (save space/attention)
- Always provide loading feedback for async operations

### Cards

Cards are flexible, container-like components for organizing and displaying content. They're one of Bootstrap's most versatile components.

**BASIC: Simple Card Structure**
```html
<div class="card">
  <img src="image.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Product">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Card Title</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Short description of content goes here.</p>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Learn More</a>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Card Anatomy:**
- `.card`: Container
- `.card-img-top`: Image at top
- `.card-body`: Padding container for content
- `.card-title`: Card heading
- `.card-text`: Body text

**INTERMEDIATE: Card with Header & Footer**
```html
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-header bg-light">
    Card Header (meta info, icons)
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Main Title</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Body content and description.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card-footer text-muted">
    Footer (timestamps, links, etc)
  </div>
</div>
```

**INTERMEDIATE: Card Grid Layout**
```html
<!-- Responsive card grid: 1 on mobile, 2 on tablet, 3 on desktop -->
<div class="row g-3"><!-- g-3 adds consistent spacing -->
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
    <div class="card h-100"><!-- h-100 makes all cards same height -->
      <img src="image1.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Product 1">
      <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
        <h5 class="card-title">Product 1</h5>
        <p class="card-text flex-grow-1">Description text...</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary mt-auto">Add to Cart</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
    <div class="card h-100">
      <img src="image2.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Product 2">
      <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
        <h5 class="card-title">Product 2</h5>
        <p class="card-text flex-grow-1">Description text...</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary mt-auto">Add to Cart</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
    <div class="card h-100">
      <img src="image3.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="Product 3">
      <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column">
        <h5 class="card-title">Product 3</h5>
        <p class="card-text flex-grow-1">Description text...</p>
        <button class="btn btn-primary mt-auto">Add to Cart</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Key techniques:**
- `.h-100`: Make all cards same height
- `.d-flex .flex-column`: Stack content vertically
- `.flex-grow-1` on description: Push button to bottom
- `.mt-auto`: Auto margin top on button

**ADVANCED: Card with Colored Background**
```html
<!-- Alert-style card -->
<div class="card border-success">
  <div class="card-header bg-success text-white">
    Success!
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p>Operation completed successfully.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Transparent card over image -->
<div class="card" style="background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.5);">
  <div class="card-img-overlay d-flex flex-column justify-content-end text-white">
    <h5 class="card-title">Image Overlay</h5>
    <p class="card-text">Text over the image</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

**ADVANCED: Card with Complex Layout**
```html
<!-- Blog post card -->
<div class="card mb-3">
  <div class="row g-0">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <img src="blog.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded-start" alt="...">
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-8">
      <div class="card-body">
        <small class="text-muted">Dec 24, 2025</small>
        <h5 class="card-title">Blog Post Title</h5>
        <p class="card-text">Brief excerpt from the blog post...</p>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary">Read More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Profile card -->
<div class="card text-center">
  <div class="card-body">
    <img src="avatar.jpg" class="rounded-circle mb-3" alt="User" width="100">
    <h5 class="card-title">John Doe</h5>
    <p class="card-text text-muted">Web Developer</p>
    <div class="btn-group">
      <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary">Follow</button>
      <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-secondary">Message</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**ðŸ”‘ Key Points to Remember:**
- Always use semantic HTML with card structure
- Cards are responsive containers - use with grid system
- Use `.h-100` for equal-height cards in a grid
- Flexbox patterns make buttons stick to bottom
- Cards can have colored borders, backgrounds, and overlays
- Use `.card-header` and `.card-footer` for sections
- Cards are great for portfolio items, products, team members, blog posts

### Badge

```html
<!-- Basic badge -->
<span class="badge bg-primary">Primary</span>
<span class="badge bg-secondary">Secondary</span>
<span class="badge bg-success">Success</span>
<span class="badge bg-danger">Danger</span>

<!-- Pill badge (rounded) -->
<span class="badge rounded-pill bg-primary">Primary</span>

<!-- Badge on heading -->
<h1>Heading <span class="badge bg-secondary">New</span></h1>

<!-- Badge with link -->
<a href="#" class="badge bg-primary">Link badge</a>
```

### Breadcrumb

```html
<nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
  <ol class="breadcrumb">
    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="#">Home</a></li>
    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="#">Library</a></li>
    <li class="breadcrumb-item active">Data</li>
  </ol>
</nav>
```

### Pagination

```html
<nav aria-label="Page navigation">
  <ul class="pagination">
    <li class="page-item">
      <a class="page-link" href="#">Previous</a>
    </li>
    <li class="page-item"><a class="page-link" href="#">1</a></li>
    <li class="page-item active"><a class="page-link" href="#">2</a></li>
    <li class="page-item"><a class="page-link" href="#">3</a></li>
    <li class="page-item">
      <a class="page-link" href="#">Next</a>
    </li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<!-- Disabled pagination -->
<li class="page-item disabled">
  <a class="page-link" href="#">Previous</a>
</li>
```

### Progress Bar

```html
<!-- Basic progress -->
<div class="progress">
  <div class="progress-bar" style="width: 25%"></div>
</div>

<!-- Progress with label -->
<div class="progress">
  <div class="progress-bar" style="width: 25%">25%</div>
</div>

<!-- Colored progress -->
<div class="progress">
  <div class="progress-bar bg-success" style="width: 25%"></div>
</div>

<!-- Striped progress -->
<div class="progress">
  <div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped" style="width: 25%"></div>
</div>

<!-- Animated progress -->
<div class="progress">
  <div class="progress-bar progress-bar-striped progress-bar-animated" style="width: 75%"></div>
</div>

<!-- Multiple bars -->
<div class="progress">
  <div class="progress-bar bg-success" style="width: 25%"></div>
  <div class="progress-bar bg-warning" style="width: 25%"></div>
  <div class="progress-bar bg-danger" style="width: 25%"></div>
</div>
```

### Spinner (Loading indicator)

```html
<!-- Border spinner -->
<div class="spinner-border" role="status">
  <span class="visually-hidden">Loading...</span>
</div>

<!-- Colored spinner -->
<div class="spinner-border text-primary"></div>
<div class="spinner-border text-success"></div>
<div class="spinner-border text-danger"></div>

<!-- Growing spinner -->
<div class="spinner-grow" role="status">
  <span class="visually-hidden">Loading...</span>
</div>

<!-- Small spinner -->
<div class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm"></div>
<div class="spinner-grow spinner-grow-sm"></div>
```

---

## Forms

### Form Structure

```html
<form>
  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="exampleInput" class="form-label">Email address</label>
    <input type="email" class="form-control" id="exampleInput" placeholder="Enter email">
    <div class="form-text">We'll never share your email.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="examplePassword" class="form-label">Password</label>
    <input type="password" class="form-control" id="examplePassword" placeholder="Enter password">
  </div>

  <div class="mb-3 form-check">
    <input type="checkbox" class="form-check-input" id="exampleCheck">
    <label class="form-check-label" for="exampleCheck">
      Remember me
    </label>
  </div>

  <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
</form>
```

### Input Types

```html
<!-- Text input -->
<input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Text input">

<!-- Email input -->
<input type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Email input">

<!-- Password input -->
<input type="password" class="form-control" placeholder="Password input">

<!-- Number input -->
<input type="number" class="form-control" placeholder="Number input">

<!-- Textarea -->
<textarea class="form-control" rows="3" placeholder="Enter message"></textarea>

<!-- Select dropdown -->
<select class="form-select">
  <option>Select option</option>
  <option>Option 1</option>
  <option>Option 2</option>
  <option>Option 3</option>
</select>

<!-- Checkboxes -->
<div class="form-check">
  <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="check1">
  <label class="form-check-label" for="check1">
    Option 1
  </label>
</div>

<!-- Radio buttons -->
<div class="form-check">
  <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="radio" id="radio1">
  <label class="form-check-label" for="radio1">
    Option 1
  </label>
</div>
<div class="form-check">
  <input class="form-check-input" type="radio" name="radio" id="radio2">
  <label class="form-check-label" for="radio2">
    Option 2
  </label>
</div>

<!-- Toggle switch (checkbox with switch styling) -->
<div class="form-check form-switch">
  <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" id="switch1">
  <label class="form-check-label" for="switch1">
    Enable feature
  </label>
</div>

<!-- Range input -->
<label for="range" class="form-label">Example range</label>
<input type="range" class="form-range" id="range">
```

### Form States

```html
<!-- Disabled input -->
<input class="form-control" type="text" value="Disabled input" disabled>

<!-- Readonly input -->
<input class="form-control" type="text" value="Readonly input" readonly>

<!-- Valid/Invalid feedback -->
<form class="was-validated">
  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="validInput" class="form-label">Valid input</label>
    <input type="text" class="form-control is-valid" id="validInput" required>
    <div class="valid-feedback">
      Looks good!
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="invalidInput" class="form-label">Invalid input</label>
    <input type="text" class="form-control is-invalid" id="invalidInput">
    <div class="invalid-feedback">
      This is invalid.
    </div>
  </div>
</form>
```

### Form Layout

```html
<!-- Horizontal form (labels on left, inputs on right) -->
<form>
  <div class="row mb-3">
    <label for="email" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Email</label>
    <div class="col-sm-10">
      <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row mb-3">
    <label for="password" class="col-sm-2 col-form-label">Password</label>
    <div class="col-sm-10">
      <input type="password" class="form-control" id="password">
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-10 offset-sm-2">
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Sign in</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</form>

<!-- Inline form (on same line) -->
<form class="row g-3">
  <div class="col-auto">
    <label for="email" class="visually-hidden">Email</label>
    <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" placeholder="Email">
  </div>
  <div class="col-auto">
    <label for="password" class="visually-hidden">Password</label>
    <input type="password" class="form-control" id="password" placeholder="Password">
  </div>
  <div class="col-auto">
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Sign in</button>
  </div>
</form>
```

### Input Groups

```html
<!-- Input group with addon -->
<div class="input-group mb-3">
  <span class="input-group-text">@</span>
  <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Username">
</div>

<!-- Input group with button -->
<div class="input-group mb-3">
  <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Search">
  <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button">Search</button>
</div>

<!-- Input group with multiple addons -->
<div class="input-group">
  <span class="input-group-text">$</span>
  <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Amount">
  <span class="input-group-text">.00</span>
</div>
```

---

## Navigation

### Navbar

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Brand</a>
    
    <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav">
      <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
    </button>
    
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
      <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link active" href="#">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" href="#">About</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item dropdown">
          <a class="nav-link dropdown-toggle" href="#" id="navbarDropdown" role="button" data-bs-toggle="dropdown">
            Dropdown
          </a>
          <ul class="dropdown-menu" aria-labelledby="navbarDropdown">
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Action</a></li>
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Another action</a></li>
            <li><hr class="dropdown-divider"></li>
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Something else</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- Dark navbar -->
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
  <!-- Content -->
</nav>

<!-- Fixed navbar (sticky top) -->
<nav class="navbar sticky-top navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
  <!-- Content -->
</nav>

<!-- Fixed to top -->
<nav class="navbar fixed-top navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
  <!-- Content -->
</nav>
```

### Tabs & Pills

```html
<!-- Tabs -->
<ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
  <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
    <button class="nav-link active" id="home-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#home">Home</button>
  </li>
  <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
    <button class="nav-link" id="profile-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#profile">Profile</button>
  </li>
  <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
    <button class="nav-link" id="contact-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#contact">Contact</button>
  </li>
</ul>

<div class="tab-content">
  <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="home">Home content</div>
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="profile">Profile content</div>
  <div class="tab-pane fade" id="contact">Contact content</div>
</div>

<!-- Pills -->
<ul class="nav nav-pills mb-3" role="tablist">
  <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
    <button class="nav-link active" id="home-pill" data-bs-toggle="pill" data-bs-target="#home">Home</button>
  </li>
  <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
    <button class="nav-link" id="profile-pill" data-bs-toggle="pill" data-bs-target="#profile">Profile</button>
  </li>
</ul>
```

---

## Alerts & Modals

### Alerts

```html
<!-- Alert types -->
<div class="alert alert-primary">Primary alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-secondary">Secondary alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-success">Success alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-danger">Danger alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-warning">Warning alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-info">Info alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-light">Light alert</div>
<div class="alert alert-dark">Dark alert</div>

<!-- Alert with close button -->
<div class="alert alert-warning alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert">
  <strong>Warning!</strong> You should check this message.
  <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="alert"></button>
</div>

<!-- Alert with title and content -->
<div class="alert alert-success">
  <h4 class="alert-heading">Well done!</h4>
  <p>Message content goes here.</p>
</div>
```

### Modals

```html
<!-- Modal button trigger -->
<button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleModal">
  Launch modal
</button>

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="exampleModal" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title">Modal title</h5>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        Modal content goes here...
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">Save changes</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Large modal -->
<div class="modal-dialog modal-lg"></div>

<!-- Small modal -->
<div class="modal-dialog modal-sm"></div>

<!-- Centered modal -->
<div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered"></div>

<!-- Scrollable modal -->
<div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-scrollable"></div>
```

### Tooltips & Popovers

```html
<!-- Tooltip -->
<button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" title="Tooltip text">
  Hover me
</button>

<script>
  const tooltipTriggerList = [].slice.call(document.querySelectorAll('[data-bs-toggle="tooltip"]'));
  tooltipTriggerList.map(tooltipTriggerEl => new bootstrap.Tooltip(tooltipTriggerEl));
</script>

<!-- Popover -->
<button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-toggle="popover" title="Popover title" data-bs-content="Popover content">
  Click me
</button>

<script>
  const popoverTriggerList = [].slice.call(document.querySelectorAll('[data-bs-toggle="popover"]'));
  popoverTriggerList.map(popoverTriggerEl => new bootstrap.Popover(popoverTriggerEl));
</script>
```

---

## Utilities

### Display

```html
<!-- Display utilities -->
<div class="d-block">Block display</div>
<div class="d-inline">Inline display</div>
<div class="d-inline-block">Inline-block display</div>
<div class="d-flex">Flex display</div>
<div class="d-none">Hidden (display: none)</div>

<!-- Responsive display -->
<div class="d-none d-md-block">Hidden on mobile, visible on md and up</div>
<div class="d-md-none">Visible on mobile, hidden on md and up</div>

<!-- Print display -->
<div class="d-print-none">Not printed</div>
<div class="d-print-block">Shown only in print</div>
```

### Visibility

```html
<!-- Visibility utilities -->
<div class="visible">Visible</div>
<div class="invisible">Invisible but takes space</div>

<!-- Screen reader only (accessible) -->
<span class="visually-hidden">Screen readers only</span>
```

### Overflow

```html
<div class="overflow-auto">Auto overflow</div>
<div class="overflow-hidden">Overflow hidden</div>
<div class="overflow-visible">Overflow visible</div>
```

### Sizing

```html
<!-- Width utilities -->
<div class="w-25">Width 25%</div>
<div class="w-50">Width 50%</div>
<div class="w-75">Width 75%</div>
<div class="w-100">Width 100%</div>
<div class="w-auto">Width auto</div>

<!-- Max width -->
<div class="mw-100">Max width 100%</div>

<!-- Height utilities -->
<div class="h-25">Height 25%</div>
<div class="h-50">Height 50%</div>
<div class="h-75">Height 75%</div>
<div class="h-100">Height 100%</div>

<!-- Viewport units -->
<div class="min-vw-100">Min viewport width 100%</div>
<div class="vh-100">Viewport height 100%</div>
```

---

## Flexbox Utilities

Flexbox utilities for flexible layouts:

```html
<!-- Display flex -->
<div class="d-flex">
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
</div>

<!-- Flex direction -->
<div class="d-flex flex-row">Row (default)</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-row-reverse">Row reverse</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-column">Column</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-column-reverse">Column reverse</div>

<!-- Justify content (horizontal alignment) -->
<div class="d-flex justify-content-start">Start</div>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">Center</div>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-end">End</div>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-between">Between</div>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-around">Around</div>

<!-- Align items (vertical alignment) -->
<div class="d-flex align-items-start">Start</div>
<div class="d-flex align-items-center">Center</div>
<div class="d-flex align-items-end">End</div>
<div class="d-flex align-items-baseline">Baseline</div>
<div class="d-flex align-items-stretch">Stretch</div>

<!-- Flex wrap -->
<div class="d-flex flex-wrap">Wrap items</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-nowrap">No wrap (default)</div>
<div class="d-flex flex-wrap-reverse">Wrap reverse</div>

<!-- Flex grow/shrink -->
<div class="d-flex">
  <div class="flex-grow-1">Grows to fill space</div>
  <div>Normal size</div>
</div>

<!-- Gap (spacing between items) -->
<div class="d-flex gap-2">
  <div>Item 1</div>
  <div>Item 2</div>
  <div>Item 3</div>
</div>
```

---

## Spacing Utilities

Margin and padding utilities:

```html
<!-- Margin utilities (m = margin) -->
<div class="m-0">Margin 0</div>
<div class="m-1">Margin 0.25rem</div>
<div class="m-2">Margin 0.5rem</div>
<div class="m-3">Margin 1rem</div>
<div class="m-4">Margin 1.5rem</div>
<div class="m-5">Margin 3rem</div>

<!-- Margin directions -->
<div class="mt-3">Margin top 3</div>
<div class="mb-3">Margin bottom 3</div>
<div class="ms-3">Margin start 3</div>
<div class="me-3">Margin end 3</div>
<div class="mx-3">Margin left & right 3</div>
<div class="my-3">Margin top & bottom 3</div>

<!-- Padding utilities (p = padding) -->
<div class="p-3">Padding 1rem</div>
<div class="pt-3">Padding top 3</div>
<div class="pb-3">Padding bottom 3</div>
<div class="ps-3">Padding start 3</div>
<div class="pe-3">Padding end 3</div>
<div class="px-3">Padding left & right 3</div>
<div class="py-3">Padding top & bottom 3</div>

<!-- Auto margin (centering) -->
<div class="mx-auto">Centered with auto margins</div>

<!-- Responsive spacing -->
<div class="m-3 m-md-5">Margin 3 on mobile, 5 on medium+</div>
<div class="p-2 p-lg-4">Padding 2 on mobile, 4 on large+</div>

<!-- Negative margin -->
<div class="m-n2">Negative margin</div>
```

---

## Best Practices

### 1. Mobile-First Approach

Always start with mobile layout, then enhance for larger screens:

```html
<!-- Mobile first: Single column -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12">Full width on mobile</div>
  <div class="col-12">Full width on mobile</div>
</div>

<!-- Enhanced for tablet and up -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6">Half width on tablet+</div>
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6">Half width on tablet+</div>
</div>

<!-- Enhanced for desktop -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">1/3 width on desktop+</div>
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">1/3 width on desktop+</div>
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">1/3 width on desktop+</div>
</div>
```

### 2. Use Semantic HTML

Always use meaningful HTML elements with Bootstrap classes:

```html
<!-- Good -->
<header class="navbar">Navigation</header>
<main class="container">Content</main>
<footer class="bg-light">Footer</footer>

<!-- Bad -->
<div class="navbar">Navigation</div>
<div class="container">Content</div>
<div class="bg-light">Footer</div>
```

### 3. Customization with CSS Variables

Override Bootstrap's default values:

```css
:root {
  --bs-primary: #007bff;
  --bs-secondary: #6c757d;
  --bs-success: #28a745;
  --bs-danger: #dc3545;
  --bs-warning: #ffc107;
  --bs-info: #17a2b8;
  --bs-light: #f8f9fa;
  --bs-dark: #343a40;
}
```

### 4. Don't Overuse Classes

Keep your HTML clean:

```html
<!-- Good: Meaningful and concise -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">Card</div>
</div>

<!-- Bad: Too many utility classes -->
<div class="d-flex flex-row justify-content-center align-items-center">
  Card
</div>
```

### 5. Accessibility

Always consider accessibility:

```html
<!-- Alt text for images -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Descriptive text">

<!-- Proper heading hierarchy -->
<h1>Main heading</h1>
<h2>Subheading</h2>

<!-- ARIA labels for screen readers -->
<button class="btn btn-primary" aria-label="Close menu">Ã—</button>

<!-- Form labels -->
<label for="email" class="form-label">Email</label>
<input type="email" class="form-control" id="email">

<!-- Skip to main content link -->
<a href="#main" class="visually-hidden-focusable">Skip to main content</a>
<main id="main"></main>
```

### 6. Performance

Keep your Bootstrap bundle lightweight:

```html
<!-- Use Bootstrap CDN for single file -->
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

<!-- OR customize with npm (remove unused components) -->
<!-- Import only what you need from Bootstrap source files -->
```

### 7. Testing on Real Devices

Always test:
- Mobile phones (iOS, Android)
- Tablets (iPad, Android tablets)
- Desktop browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Different screen sizes and orientations

### 8. CSS Specificity

Don't override Bootstrap with higher specificity:

```css
/* Bad: Too specific -->
.navbar .navbar-brand .text { color: red; }

/* Good: Keep specificity low -->
.custom-brand { color: red; }
```

---

## Advanced Concepts & Patterns

### Responsive Tables

```html
<!-- Responsive table wrapper (scrolls horizontally on small screens) -->
<div class="table-responsive">
  <table class="table table-striped table-hover">
    <thead class="table-dark">
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Email</th>
        <th>Status</th>
        <th>Actions</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>John Doe</td>
        <td>john@example.com</td>
        <td><span class="badge bg-success">Active</span></td>
        <td>
          <button class="btn btn-sm btn-warning">Edit</button>
          <button class="btn btn-sm btn-danger">Delete</button>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```

### Custom Components with Bootstrap

```html
<!-- Status badge component -->
<div class="d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2">
  <span class="badge rounded-pill bg-success">Active</span>
  <small class="text-muted">Since Dec 24, 2025</small>
</div>

<!-- Info box component -->
<div class="p-3 border-start border-primary border-4 bg-light">
  <h6 class="text-primary mb-2">Pro Tip</h6>
  <p class="mb-0">Use utility classes to create custom components quickly.</p>
</div>

<!-- Feature list component -->
<ul class="list-unstyled">
  <li class="mb-2">
    <i class="bi bi-check-circle text-success me-2"></i>
    <strong>Fast</strong> - Optimized performance
  </li>
  <li class="mb-2">
    <i class="bi bi-check-circle text-success me-2"></i>
    <strong>Responsive</strong> - Works on all devices
  </li>
  <li class="mb-2">
    <i class="bi bi-check-circle text-success me-2"></i>
    <strong>Accessible</strong> - WCAG compliant
  </li>
</ul>
```

---

## Interview Questions

### Q1: What is Bootstrap and why use it?

**Answer:**

Bootstrap is a popular front-end framework that provides:
- Pre-built responsive components
- 12-column grid system
- CSS utilities for spacing, colors, sizing
- JavaScript plugins for interactivity
- Mobile-first approach
- Excellent documentation

**Benefits:**
- Rapid development
- Responsive by default
- Consistency across projects
- Large community support
- Easy customization

---

### Q2: Explain the Bootstrap grid system.

**Answer:**

Bootstrap uses a **12-column responsive grid system**:

- **Container:** Wraps rows and columns
- **Row:** Wrapper for columns
- **Column:** Takes up space in 12-column grid
- **Gutters:** Space between columns

```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">Column</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Key features:**
- Mobile-first approach
- Responsive breakpoints (sm, md, lg, xl, xxl)
- Equal-width columns with `.col`
- Flexible sizing with column classes
- Offset and reordering capabilities

---

### Q3: What are Bootstrap breakpoints?

**Answer:**

Breakpoints are screen sizes where the layout changes:

| Breakpoint | Class | Size |
|-----------|-------|------|
| Extra Small | - | < 576px |
| Small | sm | â‰¥ 576px |
| Medium | md | â‰¥ 768px |
| Large | lg | â‰¥ 992px |
| X-Large | xl | â‰¥ 1200px |
| 2X-Large | xxl | â‰¥ 1400px |

Used for responsive design:
```html
<div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
  Full width on mobile, half on tablet, 1/3 on desktop
</div>
```

---

### Q4: How do you customize Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

**Method 1: CSS Variables**
```css
:root {
  --bs-primary: #007bff;
  --bs-secondary: #6c757d;
}
```

**Method 2: Override with Custom CSS**
```css
.btn-primary {
  background-color: #custom-color;
}
```

**Method 3: Use Sass**
```scss
$primary: #007bff;
@import "bootstrap/scss/bootstrap";
```

**Method 4: npm with custom build**
```bash
npm install bootstrap
// Import and customize source files
```

---

### Q5: What's the difference between container and container-fluid?

**Answer:**

| Property | container | container-fluid |
|----------|-----------|-----------------|
| Width | Responsive (changes at breakpoints) | 100% of viewport |
| Max width | Limited (540px, 720px, etc.) | No max width |
| Use case | Most layouts | Full-width designs |

```html
<!-- Fixed width container -->
<div class="container">
  Width: 100% < 576px, 540px (sm), 720px (md), 960px (lg)
</div>

<!-- Full width container -->
<div class="container-fluid">
  Width: Always 100%
</div>
```

---

### Q6: How do you create a responsive card grid?

**Answer:**

```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <!-- 1 column on mobile, 2 on tablet, 3 on desktop -->
    <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
      <div class="card">
        <img src="image.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Card title</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Card content</p>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Button</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- Repeat for more cards -->
  </div>
</div>
```

---

### Q7: Explain Bootstrap components.

**Answer:**

Bootstrap provides pre-built components:

- **Buttons:** `.btn`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-outline-*`
- **Cards:** `.card`, `.card-body`, `.card-title`
- **Forms:** `.form-control`, `.form-select`, `.form-check`
- **Navigation:** `.navbar`, `.nav`, `.breadcrumb`
- **Alerts:** `.alert`, `.alert-primary`, `.alert-dismissible`
- **Modals:** `.modal`, `.modal-dialog`, `.modal-content`
- **Badges:** `.badge`, `.badge-primary`
- **Progress:** `.progress`, `.progress-bar`
- **Spinners:** `.spinner-border`, `.spinner-grow`

Each component is fully styled and accessible.

---

### Q8: How do you handle form validation in Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

```html
<form class="needs-validation" novalidate>
  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="email" class="form-label">Email</label>
    <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" required>
    <div class="invalid-feedback">
      Please provide a valid email.
    </div>
  </div>

  <button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<script>
  // Enable Bootstrap validation feedback
  (() => {
    'use strict';
    const forms = document.querySelectorAll('.needs-validation');
    Array.from(forms).forEach(form => {
      form.addEventListener('submit', event => {
        if (!form.checkValidity()) {
          event.preventDefault();
          event.stopPropagation();
        }
        form.classList.add('was-validated');
      }, false);
    });
  })();
</script>
```

---

### Q9: How do you create a responsive navbar?

**Answer:**

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">Brand</a>
    
    <!-- Hamburger menu button for mobile -->
    <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav">
      <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
    </button>
    
    <!-- Navigation items (hidden on mobile, visible on lg+) -->
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
      <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link active" href="#">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" href="#">About</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item dropdown">
          <a class="nav-link dropdown-toggle" href="#" id="navDropdown" role="button" data-bs-toggle="dropdown">
            Dropdown
          </a>
          <ul class="dropdown-menu" aria-labelledby="navDropdown">
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Link 1</a></li>
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Link 2</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>
```

**Key points:**
- `navbar-expand-lg`: Collapse on small screens
- `navbar-toggler`: Hamburger menu button
- `collapse navbar-collapse`: Toggle this section
- `data-bs-toggle="collapse"`: JS toggle functionality

---

### Q10: What are Bootstrap utilities and how do you use them?

**Answer:**

Bootstrap utilities are helper classes for common CSS properties:

**Spacing:**
```html
<div class="m-3">Margin 1rem</div>
<div class="p-2">Padding 0.5rem</div>
<div class="mx-auto">Centered with auto margins</div>
```

**Display:**
```html
<div class="d-flex">Flex display</div>
<div class="d-none d-md-block">Hidden on mobile, visible on md+</div>
```

**Text:**
```html
<p class="text-center">Center aligned</p>
<p class="text-danger">Red text</p>
<p class="fw-bold">Bold text</p>
```

**Sizing:**
```html
<div class="w-100">Width 100%</div>
<div class="h-50">Height 50%</div>
```

**Advantages:**
- Rapid development
- Consistency
- No need to write custom CSS
- Responsive support

---

### Q11: How do you center content with Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

**Method 1: Flexbox**
```html
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center" style="height: 100vh;">
  <div>Centered content</div>
</div>
```

**Method 2: Grid with offset**
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6 offset-md-3">
      Centered content
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Method 3: Auto margins**
```html
<div class="mx-auto" style="width: 300px;">
  Centered content
</div>
```

**Method 4: Text center**
```html
<div class="text-center">
  Centered text
</div>
```

---

### Q12: What are the key Bootstrap 5 changes from Bootstrap 4?

**Answer:**

**Key Changes:**
1. **Removed jQuery:** Now uses vanilla JavaScript
2. **CSS Variables:** Easy customization
3. **RTL Support:** Built-in for right-to-left languages
4. **Improved utilities:** More comprehensive
5. **Updated components:** Better design and functionality
6. **Renamed classes:** e.g., `.custom-control` â†’ `.form-check`
7. **Removed IE support:** Modern browsers only
8. **Improved grid:** More flexible with new options

**Migration tips:**
- Test thoroughly on all browsers
- Update deprecated classes
- Use new CSS variable system
- Remove jQuery dependencies
- Update CDN links

---

### Q13: How do you handle responsive images in Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

```html
<!-- Responsive image -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="...">
<!-- Scales with parent width, max 100% -->

<!-- Rounded image -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="rounded" alt="...">
<img src="image.jpg" class="rounded-circle" alt="...">

<!-- Image with thumbnail -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="img-thumbnail" alt="...">

<!-- Picture element for art direction -->
<picture>
  <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="large.jpg">
  <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="medium.jpg">
  <img src="small.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="...">
</picture>

<!-- Background image -->
<div class="bg-image" style="background-image: url('image.jpg'); height: 300px;">
  Content
</div>
```

---

### Q14: How do you create accessible Bootstrap components?

**Answer:**

```html
<!-- Proper labels for forms -->
<label for="email" class="form-label">Email address</label>
<input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" aria-describedby="emailHelp">
<div id="emailHelp" class="form-text">We'll never share your email.</div>

<!-- ARIA labels for buttons without text -->
<button class="btn btn-close" aria-label="Close"></button>

<!-- Skip to main content link -->
<a href="#main" class="visually-hidden-focusable">Skip to main content</a>
<main id="main">Content</main>

<!-- Semantic HTML -->
<header class="navbar">Navigation</header>
<main>Main content</main>
<footer>Footer</footer>

<!-- Focus indicators for keyboard navigation -->
<a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Link</a>

<!-- Alt text for images -->
<img src="image.jpg" alt="Descriptive text" class="img-fluid">

<!-- Proper heading hierarchy -->
<h1>Main heading</h1>
<h2>Subheading</h2>
<h3>Sub-subheading</h3>
```

---

### Q15: How do you customize Bootstrap with Sass?

**Answer:**

```scss
// 1. Override Bootstrap's default variables BEFORE importing
$primary: #007bff;
$secondary: #6c757d;
$success: #28a745;
$danger: #dc3545;

// 2. Import Bootstrap functions first
@import "../../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/functions";

// 3. Override more variables
$enable-shadows: true;
$enable-gradients: true;

// 4. Import the rest of Bootstrap
@import "../../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/variables";
@import "../../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/mixins";
@import "../../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/root";
@import "../../node_modules/bootstrap/scss/reboot";
// ... import other files as needed

// 5. Add your custom styles
.custom-class {
  color: $primary;
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Full control over Bootstrap
- Smaller bundle size (only what you need)
- Easy variable customization
- Access to Bootstrap mixins and functions

---

### Q16: What's the difference between Bootstrap classes and utility classes?

**Answer:**

**Bootstrap Component Classes:**
- Pre-built components with complex styling
- Combine multiple properties (color, padding, border, etc.)
- Examples: `.card`, `.navbar`, `.btn`, `.modal`
- Use for major UI elements
- Less flexible but more opinionated

```html
<!-- Component class -->
<div class="card">
  <div class="card-header">Title</div>
  <div class="card-body">Content</div>
</div>
```

**Utility Classes:**
- Single-purpose, low-level classes
- Apply one or two CSS properties
- Examples: `.m-3` (margin), `.text-center`, `.d-flex`
- Use for custom styling and quick layouts
- Highly flexible and composable

```html
<!-- Utility classes -->
<div class="p-3 bg-light text-center rounded">
  Custom styled content
</div>
```

**When to Use:**
- **Components:** Main layout elements, standard patterns
- **Utilities:** Spacing, alignment, sizing, responsive adjustments
- **Combined:** Most real-world scenarios mix both approaches

---

### Q17: How do you make images responsive in Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

```html
<!-- Responsive image (scales with container) -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Description">
<!-- Max-width: 100%, height: auto -->

<!-- Responsive with max-width limit -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="img-fluid" style="max-width: 500px;" alt="...">

<!-- Rounded image -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="rounded" alt="...">
<img src="image.jpg" class="rounded-circle" alt="...">
<img src="image.jpg" class="rounded-5" alt="...">

<!-- Thumbnail style -->
<img src="image.jpg" class="img-thumbnail" alt="...">

<!-- Picture element for art direction (responsive images) -->
<picture>
  <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" srcset="large.jpg">
  <source media="(min-width: 768px)" srcset="medium.jpg">
  <img src="small.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="...">
</picture>

<!-- Background image responsive -->
<div class="bg-image" style="background-image: url('image.jpg'); 
  background-position: center; background-size: cover; height: 400px;">
  Content over image
</div>
```

**Key Concepts:**
- `.img-fluid` = `max-width: 100%; height: auto;`
- Always include `alt` attribute for accessibility
- Use `srcset` for responsive image selection
- Background images need height set explicitly

---

### Q18: How do you handle Bootstrap's default spacing values?

**Answer:**

**Spacing Scale (rem units):**
```
0 = 0
1 = 0.25rem = 4px
2 = 0.5rem = 8px
3 = 1rem = 16px
4 = 1.5rem = 24px
5 = 3rem = 48px
```

**Margin Utilities:**
```html
<!-- Margin on all sides -->
<div class="m-0">No margin</div>
<div class="m-3">Margin 1rem on all sides</div>
<div class="m-5">Margin 3rem on all sides</div>

<!-- Margin on specific sides -->
<div class="mt-3">Top margin</div>
<div class="mb-3">Bottom margin</div>
<div class="ms-3">Left margin (start)</div>
<div class="me-3">Right margin (end)</div>

<!-- Margin on opposite sides -->
<div class="mx-3">Horizontal margins (left + right)</div>
<div class="my-3">Vertical margins (top + bottom)</div>

<!-- Auto margin (centering) -->
<div class="mx-auto">Centered with auto margins</div>

<!-- Negative margins (Bootstrap 5) -->
<div class="m-n3">Negative margin (pulls back by 1rem)</div>
```

**Padding Utilities:**
```html
<div class="p-3">Padding 1rem on all sides</div>
<div class="pt-4">Top padding 1.5rem</div>
<div class="px-5">Left/right padding 3rem</div>
```

**Responsive Spacing:**
```html
<!-- Different spacing at different breakpoints -->
<div class="p-2 p-md-4 p-lg-5">
  Padding 0.5rem mobile, 1.5rem tablet, 3rem desktop
</div>

<div class="m-1 m-sm-2 m-md-3 m-lg-4 m-xl-5">
  Progressive margin increase
</div>
```

---

### Q19: How do you create a dark mode in Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

**Bootstrap 5 Dark Mode (CSS Variables):**

```html
<!-- HTML -->
<body data-bs-theme="dark">
  <!-- Content automatically uses dark colors -->
</body>

<!-- Toggle button -->
<button onclick="toggleDarkMode()">Toggle Dark Mode</button>
```

```javascript
// JavaScript
function toggleDarkMode() {
  const html = document.documentElement;
  const current = html.getAttribute('data-bs-theme');
  const newTheme = current === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark';
  html.setAttribute('data-bs-theme', newTheme);
  localStorage.setItem('theme', newTheme);
}

// Load saved theme on page load
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  const saved = localStorage.getItem('theme') || 'light';
  document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-bs-theme', saved);
});
```

**Custom Dark Mode Styles:**

```css
/* Override Bootstrap variables for dark mode */
[data-bs-theme="dark"] {
  --bs-primary: #0d6efd;
  --bs-secondary: #6c757d;
  --bs-success: #198754;
  --bs-bg-rgb: 33, 37, 41;
  --bs-text-rgb: 248, 249, 250;
}
```

**Component-specific dark mode:**

```html
<div class="bg-light" data-bs-theme="light">
  Light mode section
</div>

<div class="bg-dark text-white" data-bs-theme="dark">
  Dark mode section
</div>
```

---

### Q20: What are Bootstrap's accessibility features?

**Answer:**

**ARIA Labels & Roles:**

```html
<!-- Semantic HTML -->
<header class="navbar">Navigation</header>
<main>Main content</main>
<footer>Footer</footer>

<!-- ARIA labels for screen readers -->
<button class="btn-close" aria-label="Close menu"></button>

<!-- Form labels -->
<label for="email" class="form-label">Email</label>
<input type="email" class="form-control" id="email">

<!-- Describe input -->
<input type="password" aria-describedby="passwordHelp">
<small id="passwordHelp" class="form-text text-muted">
  Must be 8+ characters
</small>
```

**Screen Reader Only Content:**

```html
<!-- Content visible to screen readers only -->
<span class="visually-hidden">Loading...</span>

<!-- Focusable screen reader content -->
<a href="#main" class="visually-hidden-focusable">
  Skip to main content
</a>
<main id="main">Main content</main>
```

**Focus Management:**

```html
<!-- Visible focus indicators -->
<a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Link (has focus styles)</a>

<!-- Focusable disabled button -->
<button disabled>Disabled</button>

<!-- Tab order -->
<form>
  <input type="text" tabindex="1">
  <input type="email" tabindex="2">
  <button tabindex="3">Submit</button>
</form>
```

**Heading Hierarchy:**

```html
<!-- Proper heading structure (not for styling) -->
<h1>Main Page Title</h1>
<h2>Section 1</h2>
<h3>Subsection 1.1</h3>
<h2>Section 2</h2>
```

**Color Contrast:**
- Use semantic colors (primary, success, danger)
- Text on colored backgrounds meets WCAG AA (4.5:1)
- Icons + text for important information

**Form Accessibility:**
```html
<form>
  <!-- Always label form inputs -->
  <label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label>
  <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" required>
  
  <!-- Required field indicator -->
  <span aria-label="required">*</span>
  
  <!-- Error messages -->
  <div class="invalid-feedback" role="alert">
    Name is required
  </div>
</form>
```

---

### Q21: How do you build a responsive navigation menu with Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

```html
<!-- Full responsive navbar -->
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <!-- Brand -->
    <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">MyWebsite</a>
    
    <!-- Toggle button for mobile -->
    <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav" aria-controls="navbarNav" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
      <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
    </button>
    
    <!-- Collapsible menu -->
    <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
      <!-- Left aligned items -->
      <ul class="navbar-nav">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link active" href="#">Home</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" href="#">About</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item dropdown">
          <a class="nav-link dropdown-toggle" href="#" id="servicesDropdown" role="button" data-bs-toggle="dropdown">
            Services
          </a>
          <ul class="dropdown-menu" aria-labelledby="servicesDropdown">
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Web Design</a></li>
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Development</a></li>
            <li><hr class="dropdown-divider"></li>
            <li><a class="dropdown-item" href="#">Consulting</a></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      
      <!-- Right aligned items -->
      <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="nav-link" href="#">Contact</a>
        </li>
        <li class="nav-item">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#">Get Started</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>
```

**Navbar Variations:**

```html
<!-- Dark navbar (dark background, light text) -->
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
  <!-- Content -->
</nav>

<!-- Sticky navbar (stays at top during scroll) -->
<nav class="navbar sticky-top navbar-expand-lg bg-light">
  <!-- Content -->
</nav>

<!-- Fixed navbar (always at top) -->
<nav class="navbar fixed-top navbar-expand-lg bg-light">
  <!-- Content -->
</nav>
<!-- Add padding to body for fixed navbar -->
<body style="padding-top: 56px;">
```

---

### Q22: What's the best way to handle form validation in Bootstrap?

**Answer:**

**HTML5 Validation with Bootstrap Styling:**

```html
<form class="needs-validation" novalidate>
  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="email" class="form-label">Email</label>
    <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" required>
    <div class="invalid-feedback">
      Please provide a valid email address.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-3">
    <label for="password" class="form-label">Password</label>
    <input type="password" class="form-control" id="password" required>
    <div class="invalid-feedback">
      Password is required.
    </div>
  </div>

  <button class="btn btn-primary" type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<script>
  // Enable Bootstrap validation
  (() => {
    'use strict';
    const forms = document.querySelectorAll('.needs-validation');
    Array.from(forms).forEach(form => {
      form.addEventListener('submit', event => {
        if (!form.checkValidity()) {
          event.preventDefault();
          event.stopPropagation();
        }
        form.classList.add('was-validated');
      }, false);
    });
  })();
</script>
```

**Real-time Validation:**

```html
<div class="mb-3">
  <label for="username" class="form-label">Username</label>
  <input type="text" class="form-control" id="username">
  <div class="valid-feedback">Username looks good!</div>
  <div class="invalid-feedback">Username is taken.</div>
</div>

<script>
  const input = document.getElementById('username');
  input.addEventListener('blur', async () => {
    const value = input.value;
    const isAvailable = await checkUsername(value);
    
    input.classList.remove('is-valid', 'is-invalid');
    input.classList.add(isAvailable ? 'is-valid' : 'is-invalid');
  });

  async function checkUsername(username) {
    const response = await fetch(`/api/check-username?u=${username}`);
    const data = await response.json();
    return data.available;
  }
</script>
```

---

### Q23: How do you optimize Bootstrap bundle size?

**Answer:**

**Method 1: Use only CSS (without JavaScript):**
```html
<!-- Only CSS, no JavaScript functionality -->
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
<!-- Size: ~20KB gzipped -->
```

**Method 2: CDN vs NPM:**
```bash
# CDN approach (simple, no build step)
<!-- Single file, includes everything -->

# NPM approach (allows customization)
npm install bootstrap
# Import only what you need
```

**Method 3: Custom Sass Build (recommended for production):**

```scss
// Import only Bootstrap components you use
@import "bootstrap/scss/functions";
@import "bootstrap/scss/variables";
@import "bootstrap/scss/variables-dark";
@import "bootstrap/scss/mixins";
@import "bootstrap/scss/reboot";

// Import only needed components
@import "bootstrap/scss/containers";
@import "bootstrap/scss/grid";
@import "bootstrap/scss/tables";
@import "bootstrap/scss/forms";
@import "bootstrap/scss/buttons";
@import "bootstrap/scss/utilities/api";

// Skip components you don't use:
// @import "bootstrap/scss/spinners";
// @import "bootstrap/scss/modal";
// etc.
```

**Method 4: PurgeCSS / Tree Shaking:**
```javascript
// webpack.config.js
const PurgeCSSPlugin = require('purgecss-webpack-plugin');
const glob = require('glob-all');

module.exports = {
  plugins: [
    new PurgeCSSPlugin({
      paths: glob.sync([
        path.join(__dirname, 'src/**/*.html'),
        path.join(__dirname, 'src/**/*.vue'),
      ]),
    }),
  ],
};
```

**Size Comparison:**
- Bootstrap CSS only: ~20KB
- Bootstrap JS + Popper: ~37KB
- Full CDN bundle: ~67KB
- Custom build (common components): ~15-25KB

---

### Q24: How do you handle Bootstrap on Angular/Vue/React projects?

**Answer:**

**Angular Integration:**

```bash
# Install Bootstrap
npm install bootstrap
```

```typescript
// angular.json
{
  "projects": {
    "my-app": {
      "architect": {
        "build": {
          "options": {
            "styles": [
              "node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css",
              "src/styles.css"
            ],
            "scripts": [
              "node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**React Integration:**

```bash
npm install bootstrap react-bootstrap
```

```jsx
// Use Bootstrap components as React components
import Button from 'react-bootstrap/Button';
import Container from 'react-bootstrap/Container';
import Row from 'react-bootstrap/Row';
import Col from 'react-bootstrap/Col';

function App() {
  return (
    <Container>
      <Row>
        <Col md={6}>
          <Button variant="primary">Click me</Button>
        </Col>
      </Row>
    </Container>
  );
}
```

**Vue Integration:**

```bash
npm install bootstrap
```

```vue
<template>
  <div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <button class="btn btn-primary">Click me</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
  name: 'App'
}
</script>

<style scoped>
@import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';
</style>
```

---

### Q25: What are common Bootstrap pitfalls to avoid?

**Answer:**

**1. Not Using Container Wrapper**
```html
<!-- âŒ Bad: Row without container -->
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-6">Column</div>
</div>

<!-- âœ… Good: Container wraps row -->
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-6">Column</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**2. Overusing Utilities (Bloated HTML)**
```html
<!-- âŒ Bad: Too many utility classes -->
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center m-3 p-4 bg-light text-center">
  Content
</div>

<!-- âœ… Good: Use custom CSS for complex combinations -->
<style>
  .custom-box {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    margin: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>

<div class="custom-box">Content</div>
```

**3. Improper Column Structure**
```html
<!-- âŒ Bad: Column as direct child of container -->
<div class="container">
  <div class="col-6">Content</div>
</div>

<!-- âœ… Good: Row between container and column -->
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-6">Content</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

**4. Not Responsive (Breakpoint Issues)**
```html
<!-- âŒ Bad: Same width on all screens -->
<div class="col-4">Always 1/3 width</div>

<!-- âœ… Good: Responsive breakpoints -->
<div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4">
  Full on mobile, half on tablet, 1/3 on desktop
</div>
```

**5. Ignoring Accessibility**
```html
<!-- âŒ Bad: No semantic HTML or labels -->
<div class="btn btn-primary">Click</div>
<input class="form-control">

<!-- âœ… Good: Semantic HTML + labels -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">Click</button>
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input class="form-control" id="email">
```

**6. Breaking Bootstrap with Z-index**
```css
/* âŒ Bad: High arbitrary z-index breaks modals/dropdowns */
.custom-element {
  z-index: 9999;
}

/* âœ… Good: Use Bootstrap's z-index system */
.custom-element {
  z-index: var(--bs-dropdown-zindex); /* 1000 */
}
```

---

## Resources

- **Bootstrap Official:** https://getbootstrap.com
- **Bootstrap Documentation:** https://getbootstrap.com/docs
- **Bootstrap Icons:** https://icons.getbootstrap.com
- **Bootstrap Themes:** https://bootswatch.com
- **Bootstrap CDN:** https://www.jsdelivr.com/package/npm/bootstrap

